adjectives.description: overgross (comparative more overgross, superlative most overgross)

examples: […]  and to say we may not have images and call them idols, when they represent Christ and his saints, be overgross opinions to enter into your learned head, whatsoever the unlearned would tattle.

verbs.description: overgross (third-person singular simple present overgrosses, present participle overgrossing, simple past and past participle overgrossed)

entries.meaning: (aviation, transitive) To load (a plane) with too much weight, thereby impairing its ability to fly.
